                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1901</hi>
                        </date>,</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 382.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr. Squier’s
                    dispatch, No. 674, of July 22 last,<note n="a" xml:id="d345fna">Not
                        printed.</note> inclosing a copy of correspondence regarding a proposed
                    revision of the code of rules for the mixed court at Shanghai, and reporting
                    that he has requested the United States consul-general at Shanghai to confer
                    with his British and German colleagues with the view of drafting a revised code
                    for submission to the diplomatic body.</p>
                <p>In reply I have to say that the department would be glad to examine the proposed
                    code after it has been agreed upon by the consuls.,</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
